title: Google\Cloud\Compute\V1\Route
name: Route
description:
Represents a Route resource.

A route defines a path from VM instances in the VPC network to a specific destination. This destination can be inside or outside the VPC network. For more information, read the Routes overview. (== resource_for {$api_version}.routes ==)

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.compute.v1.Route

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.creation_timestamp
params.description: [Output Only] Creation timestamp in RFC3339 text format.

params.name: data.description
params.description: An optional description of this resource. Provide this field when you create the resource.

params.name: data.dest_range
params.description: The destination range of outgoing packets that this route applies to. Both IPv4 and IPv6 are supported.

params.name: data.id
params.description: [Output Only] The unique identifier for the resource. This identifier is defined by the server.

params.name: data.kind
params.description: [Output Only] Type of this resource. Always compute#routes for Route resources.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Name of the resource. Provided by the client when the resource is created. The name must be 1-63 characters long, and comply with RFC1035. Specifically, the name must be 1-63 characters long and match the regular expression [a-z]([-a-z0-9]*[a-z0-9])?. The first character must be a lowercase letter, and all following characters (except for the last character) must be a dash, lowercase letter, or digit. The last character must be a lowercase letter or digit.

params.name: data.network
params.description: Fully-qualified URL of the network that this route applies to.

params.name: data.next_hop_gateway
params.description: The URL to a gateway that should handle matching packets. You can only specify the internet gateway using a full or partial valid URL: projects/project/global/gateways/default-internet-gateway

params.name: data.next_hop_ilb
params.description: The URL to a forwarding rule of type loadBalancingScheme=INTERNAL that should handle matching packets or the IP address of the forwarding Rule. For example, the following are all valid URLs: - 10.128.0.56 - https://www.googleapis.com/compute/v1/projects/project/regions/region/forwardingRules/forwardingRule - regions/region/forwardingRules/forwardingRule

params.name: data.next_hop_instance
params.description: The URL to an instance that should handle matching packets. You can specify this as a full or partial URL. For example: https://www.googleapis.com/compute/v1/projects/project/zones/zone/instances/

params.name: data.next_hop_ip
params.description: The network IP address of an instance that should handle matching packets. Only IPv4 is supported.

params.name: data.next_hop_network
params.description: The URL of the local network if it should handle matching packets.

params.name: data.next_hop_peering
params.description: [Output Only] The network peering name that should handle matching packets, which should conform to RFC1035.

params.name: data.next_hop_vpn_tunnel
params.description: The URL to a VpnTunnel that should handle matching packets.

params.name: data.priority
params.description: The priority of this route. Priority is used to break ties in cases where there is more than one matching route of equal prefix length. In cases where multiple routes have equal prefix length, the one with the lowest-numbered priority value wins. The default value is 1000. The priority value must be from 0 to 65535, inclusive.

params.name: data.self_link
params.description: [Output Only] Server-defined fully-qualified URL for this resource.

params.name: data.tags
params.description: A list of instance tags to which this route applies.

params.name: data.warnings
params.description: [Output Only] If potential misconfigurations are detected for this route, this field will be populated with warning messages.
